%% Classical GoF Command — encapsulate a request as an object so it
%% can be queued, logged, undone, or replayed.
classDiagram
    class Command {
        <<interface>>
        +execute()
        +undo()
    }
    class AddLine
    class DeleteLine
    class SetCursor

    class Invoker {
        -history: Stack~Command~
        +submit(Command)
        +undo()
    }
    class Editor {
        +apply(Command)
    }

    Invoker --> "*" Command : holds
    Command <|.. AddLine
    Command <|.. DeleteLine
    Command <|.. SetCursor
    AddLine    --> Editor : invokes
    DeleteLine --> Editor
    SetCursor  --> Editor

    note for Command "In Rust: trait + enum + Box<dyn>\nfor introspectable commands,\nor Box<dyn FnOnce()> for one-shot\ndeferred work.\nPick by what you need: replay?\nundo? inspection? just delay?"
